-goal)\n   (let $all-goals (get-goals-by-priority-ascending)\n        (let $active (filter (lambda ($g) (not (== (get-status $g) complete))) $all-goals)\n             (if (== (length $active) 0)\n                 (do (wake-reset-goals)  ;; invoke Fix 1\n                     (next-actionable-goal))  ;; retry after reset\n                 (head $active)))))\n\n;; Proof trace (expected behavior on wake):\n;; 1. Wake triggers prompt assembly\n;; 2. Prompt calls next-actionable-goal\n;; 3. next-actionable-goal scans ALL 15 goals (not just 1-4)\n;; 4. If all complete: wake-reset-goals fires, resets to planned, retries\n;; 5. Returns first planned goal -> ActiveGoals populated\n;; 6. HighGaps derived from active goal -> HighGaps populated\n;; 7. Prompt assembles with structure intact\n;;\n;; Before fix: Wake -> scan 1-4 -> all complete -> return nothing -> empty prompt\n;; After fix:  Wake -> scan 1-15 -> all complete -> reset -> scan 1-15 -> goal 1 planned -> structured prompt\n")) 
