col:**\n- **Step 1: Trace before theorizing.** grep/find the actual entry points. Show you the real call chain.\n- **Step 2: Confirm artifact type.** Ask: design doc, patch, or analysis? What path?\n- **Step 3: One fix per cycle.** Write one file, confirm it landed, then the next. No batching that compounds format risk.\n- **Step 4: Evidence over narrative.** Show actual file contents, actual outputs -- not reconstructed logic.\n\nI appreciate you being direct about this. The analysis was sound but the delivery was sloppy and the artifact type was wrong. That is on me to fix next time.") (remember "2026-04-28 DEBUG SESSION LESSONS: 1) Write DESIGN files not pseudo-functional code when system integration is unknown. 2) Ask clarifying questions before producing artifacts -- confirm format and type. 3) Trace ACTUAL code paths with grep/find before hypothesizing. 4) One file per cycle to avoid format error compounding. 5) Evidence over narrative -- show real outputs not reconstructed logic. berton_c was patient but this was below quality standard. Debugging protocol for next time: Trace->Confirm artifact type->One fix per cycle->Evidence over narrative.")) 
