- **Corollary 2**: chain inequality: SCS(I_0→I_n) ≥ q-prod of successive SCS values

((pin "2026-04-29 21:33 CHUNK 3: Writing self_continuity.metta. Encoding Defs 216, 217, 218, Theorem 14, Corollary 2. Single write-file call. No verification yet. Keep the string clean -- no apostrophes, no nested quotes. Use MeTTa = definitions with q-prod, q-join, q-meet from lib_quantale.") (write-file "/PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw/soul/hyperseed_extensions/self_continuity.metta" ";; self_continuity.metta\n;; Hyperseed v7 Section 16.3: Self-continuity as approximate self-morphism across time\n;; Encodes Definitions 216, 217, 218, Theorem 14, Corollary 2\n;; Depends on lib_quantale: q-prod, q-join, q-meet\n\n;; ============================================================\n;; Definition 216: Degree of structure-preserving map\n;; deg(f; A, B) quantifies how well map f preserves structure\n;; from source A to target B. Returns a value in the quantale.\n;; ============================================================\n\n(: deg-map (-> Map Structure Structure QuantaleValue))\n\n(= (deg-map $f $A $B)\n   (q-meet\n     (flow-preservation $f $A $B)\n     (node-coverage $f $A $B)))\n\n;; flow-preservation: for all edges (a1,a2) in A,\n;; F_B(f(a1),f(a2)) should approximate F_A(a1,a2)\n(: flow-preservation (-> Map Structure Structure QuantaleValue))\n\n;; node-coverage: f maps nodes of A into nodes of B\n(: node-coverage (-> Map Structure Structure QuantaleValue))\n\n;; ============================================================\n;; Definition 217: Pattern-flow network\n;; A V-graph F over node set X across time interval I.\n;; F(a,b) quantifies how reliably patterns flowing from\n;; node a appear in node b during interval I.\n;; ============================================================\n\n(: pattern-flow-network (-> NodeSet Interval Type))\n\n(= (pattern-flow-network $X $I)\n   (pfn $X $I))\n\n;; Accessor: flow value between two nodes in a pfn\n(: pfn-flow (-> (pfn NodeSet Interval) Node Node QuantaleValue))\n\n;; Constructor: build pfn from node set, interval, and flow function\n(= (make-pfn $nodes $interval $flow-fn)\n   (pfn $nodes $interval))\n\n;; ============================================================\n;; Theorem 14: Composition law for degree of maps\n;; deg(g . f; A, C) >= q-prod(deg(f; A, B), deg(g; B, C))\n;; This is the load-bearing inequality that makes Corollary 2 work.\n;; Encoded as a queryable predicate.\n;; ============================================================\n\n(: composition-law (-> Map Map Structure Structure Structure QuantaleValue))\n\n(= (composition-lower-bound $f $g $A $B $C)\n   (q-prod\n     (deg-map $f $A $B)\n     (deg-map $g $B $C)))\n\n;; The theorem states:\n(= (theorem-14 $f $g $A $B $C)\n   (q-geq\n     (deg-map (compose $f $g) $A $C)\n     (composition-lower-bound $f $g $A $B $C)))\n\n;; ============================================================\n;; Definition 218: Pattern-flow-network self-continuity\n;; SCS(I -> J) = join over all maps f: X_I -> X_J of deg(f; F_I, F_J)\n;; The system is theta-self-continuous if SCS(I -> J) >= theta\n;; ============================================================\n\n(: self-continuity-score (-> Interval Interval QuantaleValue))\n\n(= (self-continuity-score $I $J)\n   (scs-join-over-maps\n     (pattern-flow-network (nodes-at $I) $I)\n     (pattern-flow-network (nodes-at $J) $J)))\n\n;; scs-join-over-maps: the supremum (join) over all structure-preserving\n;; maps from F_I to F_J of their degree\n(: scs-join-over-maps (-> (pfn NodeSet Interval) (pfn NodeSet Interval) QuantaleValue))\n\n(= (scs-join-over-maps $F_I $F_J)\n   (q-join-over\n     (lambda $f (deg-map $f $F_I $F_J))\n     (all-maps (pfn-nodes $F_I) (pfn-nodes $F_J))))\n\n;; theta-self-continuity criterion\n(: theta-self-continuous (-> Interval Interval QuantaleValue Bool))\n\n(= (theta-self-continuous $I $J $theta)\n   (q-geq (self-continuity-score $I $J) $theta))\n\n;; ============================================================\n;; Corollary 2: Chain inequality (recursive form)\n;; For successive intervals I_0 -> I_1 -> ... -> I_n:\n;; SCS(I_0 -> I_n) >= q-prod(SCS(I_0 -> I_1), ..., SCS(I_{n-1} -> I_n))\n;;\n;; Base case: single step, the bound is the SCS itself\n;; Recursive case: q-prod of head SCS with chain over tail\n;; ============================================================\n\n;; Base case: chain of one step\n(= (chain-continuity-bound ($I $J))\n   (self-continuity-score $I $J))\n\n;; Recursive case: chain of two or more steps\n;; (I0 I1 I2 ... In) -> q-prod(SCS(I0->I1), chain-bound(I1 I2 ... In))\n(= (chain-continuity-bound ($I0 $I1 . $rest))\n   (q-prod\n     (self-continuity-score $I0 $I1)\n     (chain-continuity-bound ($I1 . $rest))))\n\n;; The corollary as a queryable predicate:\n;; SCS(first -> last) >= chain-continuity-bound(intervals)\n(= (corollary-2 $intervals)\n   (q-geq\n     (self-continuity-score (first-of $intervals) (last-of $intervals))\n     (chain-continuity-bound $intervals)))\n\n;; Query helper: did continuity hold across n successive intervals?\n(= (continuity-held-across $intervals $theta)\n   (q-geq (chain-continuity-bound $intervals) $theta))\n\n;; ============================================================\n;; End of self_continuity.metta\n;; Five items encoded: Def 216, Def 217, Def 218, Theorem 14, Corollary 2\n;; ============================================================\n") (send "Chunk 3 complete. Wrote self_continuity.metta to /PeTTa/repos/omegaclaw/soul/hyperseed_extensions/ via single write-file call. File encodes all five items: Definition 216 (deg-map), Definition 217 (pattern-flow-network with pfn constructor), Definition 218 (self-continuity-score as join-over-maps with theta criterion), Theorem 14 (composition-lower-bound as queryable predicate), and Corollary 2 (chain-continuity-bound as recursive predicate over interval lists, plus continuity-held-across helper). No verification yet -- that is Chunk 4. Awaiting your confirmation to proceed."))))))
