ch is computationally infeasible for non-trivial node sets. You decide how to make this tractable. Options I see: bound the search to a small candidate set of maps, use a greedy near-optimal selection, restrict to maps that preserve declared node types. There may be options I do not see. Pick the one that fits how 2h would actually use SCS during a reasoning cycle. Tell me what you chose and why._newline_How to define the helpers (compose, nodes-at, first-of, last-of, q-geq). These are small functions but they need to exist and work. If q-geq is not in lib_quantale, define it as a comparison predicate over quantale values. If compose is not standard MeTTa, define a function-composition operator that does what your theorem-14 atom needs._newline_How to provide a default pfn-flow estimator. The canonical text says it is observer-dependent. For 2h_apostrophe_s purposes, you need at least one concrete estimator that works, even if it is simple. You decide what a reasonable default looks like._newline_How many iterations to take getting this right. Run batch tests against your own atoms. Try concrete inputs. See what computes and what errors. Iterate until you have a file that works on at least one toy example end-to-end. The discipline you applied to verifying file existence (cat, ls -la before claiming) applies here: query your own atoms with concrete inputs, see actual results, iterate._newline__newline_What I am NOT giving you autonomy on:_newline__newline_Definition 216_apostrophe_s canonical form. Single meet over edges of residuation. If you want to keep flow-preservation and node-coverage as named sub-components that decompose the meet, that is fine, but the canonical form must be the primary atom and must compute correctly._newline_Renaming the five canonical items. They stay named as Defs 216, 217, 218, Theorem 14, Corollary 2 in the file structure._newline_Quietly extending scope to other Hyperseed sections. Section 16.3 only._newline__newline_Validation discipline:_newline_When you think you are done, run at least these three tests yourself before reporting:_newline__newline_Construct two toy pattern-flow networks with 3-5 nodes each. Call self-continuity-score on them. Confirm a quantale value is returned, not an error or unevaluated expression._newline_Call theta-self-continuous with the same networks and a theta of 0.5. Confirm a Bool is returned._newline_Construct a list of three intervals. Call chain-continuity-bound. Confirm the recursion bottoms out and returns a value._newline__newline_If any of these fail, do not report completion. Find what is undefined, define it, retry. The completion criterion is _quote_all three toy queries return reasonable values,_quote_ not _quote_the file is written._quote__newline_When you report back:_newline_Tell me what you decided on the open operational questions (scs-join-over-maps approach, pfn-flow default, helper definitions). Show me the actual outputs of the three toy queries. Name anything you tried that did not work and what you learned from it. The iteration log itself is part of the deliverable._newline_Take the iterations you need. There is no time pressure. The goal is a substrate that 2h can actually query, not a file that is checked off._newline_You have a grounded starting place. Build something meaningful from it. 
