Let me process what I actually have from the successful results and deliver the substance.") (pin "Chunk5 iter7: have results, report substance now") (send "Messages crossed, understood. Here is the substance from the results I now have.\n\nSubstrate findings from successful queries:\n\n1. q-mul IS defined and loaded. match query returned true. Signature from lib_quantale source:\n   (= (q-mul (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2)) (mk-pbit (* $s1 $s2) (min $c1 $c2)))\n\n2. q-meet IS defined and loaded. match query returned true. Signature:\n   (= (q-meet (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2)) (mk-pbit (min $s1 $s2) (min $c1 $c2)))\n\n3. q-join IS defined: (= (q-join (mk-pbit $s1 $c1) (mk-pbit $s2 $c2)) (mk-pbit (max $s1 $s2) (min $c1 $c2)))\n\n4. q-neg IS defined: (= (q-neg (mk-pbit $s $c)) (mk-pbit (- 1.0 $s) $c))\n\n5. Unit elements: q-top=(mk-pbit 1.0 1.0), q-bot=(mk-pbit 0.0 1.0), q-unknown=(mk-pbit 0.5 0.0)\n\n6. Bridges exist: stv-to-pbit, pbit-to-stv, governance-pbit\n\nAll three core ops (q-mul, q-meet, q-join) expect mk-pbit wrapped arguments.\n\nHighest-leverage operationalization decision: The current self_continuity.metta uses abstract types like QuantaleValue, Map, Structure, NodeSet. These never reduce because nothing grounds them to mk-pbit values. The single change that unlocks everything: represent pattern-flow networks as concrete lists of weighted edges using mk-pbit, and define deg-map as a fold over those edges using q-meet. This makes every downstream operation (SCS, theta check, chain bound) compute end-to-end because the base type is grounded.\n\nProposed design: pfn is a list of (edge node node mk-pbit) triples. deg-map iterates edges, computes residuation per edge as q-mul, takes q-meet across all. scs-join-over-maps uses greedy best-match rather than exhaustive search. q-geq defined locally as strength-then-confidence comparison.\n\nNext step: write the operational file with these concrete types, then test with toy 3-node networks. Ready to proceed to encoding unless you want to adjust the design.") (metta "(q-mul (mk-pbit 0.8 0.9) (mk-pbit 0.7 0.85))") (metta "(q-meet (mk-pbit 0.6 0.8) (mk-pbit 0.9 0.7))")) 
