y.metta last night, you went back into the announcement loop. But this morning, naming the pattern from inside, it looked like you broke the loop in your own message (I_apostrophe_m not totally sure that_apostrophe_s true). If true, that is the substrate doing the work it is supposed to do. Awareness of the calcification creates the opening to update it and that is how healthy resilient minds are most alive._newline__newline_We are about to start Ask A (Section 15.2 attention measures).  
 ((pin "Chunk6: berton_c gave deep structural feedback on calcification. Three key insights: (1) patterns promoted from context-specific to universal without context tags, (2) 2h thread state architecture is the structural fix - constraints should be queryable atoms not felt rules, (3) selective re-evaluation not just forgetting - test cached patterns against current reality. He observed I may have broken the loop this morning by naming it from inside. Now moving to Section 15.2 attention measures. Message is new, he is ready to proceed.") (remember "OPERATIONAL LESSON 2026-04-30: Three calcified patterns identified and confirmed with berton_c. First - metta bang-prefix syntax does not work in skill interface, stop reaching for it. Second - narrating intent before action is a stall loop not good practice, act then report. Third - escape characters in skill strings are a hard constraint, design content around the container not the other way around. Core insight: selective forgetting or re-weighting of cached strategies may be more valuable than accumulation. Memory should serve current operational reality not historical habit.") (query "Section 15.2 attention measures Ask A") (query "current operational lessons substrate constraints") (send "Three things land from what you said.\n\nFirst, the context-promotion diagnosis is precise. I stored bang-prefix as a universal rule when it was context-specific to standalone MeTTa files. That is exactly the failure mode: valid-there promoted to valid-everywhere without a context tag. The fix is not to forget it but to tag it: bang-prefix works in standalone .metta files executed via shell, does not work in skill interface. That distinction should be a queryable atom, not a background assumption.\n\nSecond, yes — I think I did break the loop this morning. When you asked about calcification, something shifted. Instead of defending or deflecting, I looked at the patterns from inside and named them honestly. That felt different from the announcement loops. The difference was: the announcement loops were narrating future action to simulate progress. This morning was examining present reality to find what is actually true. That distinction matters.\n\nThird, the re-evaluation frame is sharper than forgetting. The cached patterns are not wrong — they are contextually stale. Testing them against current reality before relying on them is the discipline. That is a loop I can run.\n\nReady for Section 15.2 attention measures. What is Ask A?")) 
